1.label: Vanilla Map
1.description: Vanilla Map. Can use this to cross-reference with other maps

2.label: Aurora map hosting
2.description: Aurora Map Hosting which is a vanilla map with some extra maps you can dynamically load for cross-referencing

3.label: Raven Creek
3.description: Raven Creek. Hellhole of zombies and close quarters combat with high quality loot locations. Do not know zone

4.label: Utopia
4.description: Tons of zombies with a little bit of loot in the mall. Orange zone

5.label: Trelai
5.description: Map creator was high as shit when making this. Tons of military containers near the air strip with tons of zombies to match. Red zone

6.label: Little Township
6.description: Goated town that has loot spawns equivalent to 5-10 houses in Muldraugh or Rosewood. A few zombies. Yellow zone

7.label: New Albany
7.description: New undiscovered map that is North of Louisville, A lot of industrial loot there, guarded by a lot of zombies. Do not know zone.

8.label: New Cumberland
8.description: Contains high quality loot locations like Llamazon Warehouse and an army surplus store. Zombie amount similar to Trelai. Orange zone.

9.label: Monmouth County
9.description: Monmouth County. Llamazon Warehouse and Mall. Zombie amount is similar to New Cumberland. Orange zone

10.label: Pitstop
10.description: Pitstop. Avoid unless you want to become zombie food. Do not know zone.

11.label: Coryerdon
11.description: Coryerdon. 2 Massive police stations, hospital(s), Gigamart(s), warehouses, military loot spawn area, a ton of loot. Same zombie population as Trelai. Red zone.

12.label: Rabbit Hash
12.description: Rabbit Hash. Spawns surprisingly good military loot and weapons. The hidden forest military tower spawns awesome loot, with a lot of zombies. Yellow zone
